http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html

&gt; A Unicode character can also be represented in a regular-expression by using its Hex notation(hexadecimal code point value) directly as described in construct \x{...}, for example a supplementary character U+2011F can be specified as \x{2011F}, instead of two consecutive Unicode escape sequences of the surrogate pair \uD840\uDD1F.

Nevertheless, if you cannot switch to Java 7, you can extend the valuable [UnicodeEscaper](http://docs.guava-libraries.googlecode.com/git/javadoc/com/google/common/escape/UnicodeEscaper.html) provided by Guava.

